@TomSweeneyRedHat, I'm fairly sure this is how the `--volumes` flag already handles this case: https://github.com/andrewaylett/podman/blob/3cee85531c43e7c66a6428b60b73925b2fcefcac/pkg/specgen/volumes.go#L78

It looks like the `--mount` code predates the current behaviour for `--volumes` -- I'm assuming that it was missed rather than being deliberately left as-was.

I don't think I mentioned that I've at least briefly validated this locally: the Qodana invocation that I mentioned in #13756 succeeds (with an selinux caveat) when I have this patch applied.  That's no guarantee that it's _correct_ of course.
